<LP>
   NEW YORK -- American Home Products Corp. said it completed
most of the sale of its household products and depilatory
businesses to Reckitt &amp; Colman PLC.
   The pharmaceutical manufacturer said the sale of the
businesses in the U.S. and 17 other countries had closed. It
said Reckitt &amp; Colman, a London-based marketer of consumer
brands, expected to complete its purchase of the remaining
American Home operations in six other countries before the
end of 1990.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The total purchase price is $1.25 billion.
</TEXT>
